abstract: Coronavirus, India violence, South Carolina primary: Here’s what you need to know.
snippet: Coronavirus, India violence, South Carolina primary: Here’s what you need to know.
lead_paragraph: Prosecutors are deciding whether to investigate the founder and top leaders of Shincheonji Church of Jesus, whose members account for nearly 60 percent of the country’s more than 3,500 confirmed cases of the novel coronavirus, on murder and other charges.

abstract: Rudolph Giuliani and Sheldon Adelson were among those who asked President Trump to pardon a symbol of 1980s greed.
snippet: Rudolph Giuliani and Sheldon Adelson were among those who asked President Trump to pardon a symbol of 1980s greed.
lead_paragraph: Michael Milken, a symbol of 1980s greed who went to prison for securities fraud and conspiracy, was at home in Encino, Calif., on Feb. 18 when he got a phone call from the White House. President Trump was on the line with good news: Mr. Milken had been pardoned.

abstract: After suffering its worst casualties in years, Turkey is openly declaring war against the Syrian government of Bashar al-Assad.
snippet: After suffering its worst casualties in years, Turkey is openly declaring war against the Syrian government of Bashar al-Assad.
lead_paragraph: ISTANBUL — Turkey said on Sunday that it was launching a major counteroffensive against the Syrian government, for the first time openly declaring war on the government of Bashar al-Assad and steeply escalating Istanbul’s involvement in Syria’s nine-year war.

headline_main: Michael Bloomberg, a Billionaire Learning on the Job

abstract: Representative Kay Granger is in an expensive primary battle while facing accusations that she has not done enough for President Trump, who endorsed her.
snippet: Representative Kay Granger is in an expensive primary battle while facing accusations that she has not done enough for President Trump, who endorsed her.
lead_paragraph: FORT WORTH — On the heated upstairs patio of a downtown bar on a recent Friday night, dozens of Republican voters drank beers, snacked on nachos and cheered and sang along to the chorus of a disparaging ode to a liberal RINO — Republican in name only — from the swamp, who, according to the lyrics, had declared: “I’m Never Trump — you’ll never build that wall.”

abstract: Senior officials in President Donald Trump's administration on Sunday tried to calm market panic that the coronavirus could cause a global recession, saying the U.S. public had over-reacted and that stocks would rebound due to the American economy's underlying strength.
snippet: Senior officials in President Donald Trump's administration on Sunday tried to calm market panic that the coronavirus could cause a global recession, saying the U.S. public had over-reacted and that stocks would rebound due to the American economy...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senior officials in President Donald Trump's administration on Sunday tried to calm market panic that the coronavirus could cause a global recession, saying the U.S. public had over-reacted and that stocks would rebound due to the American economy's underlying strength.
headline_main: U.S. Officials Talk Down Coronavirus Market Panic, Tout Economic Strength
headline_print_headline: U.S. Officials Talk Down Coronavirus Market Panic, Tout Economic Strength

abstract: The coronavirus may have been circulating for weeks undetected in Washington state, a preliminary finding that could mean hundreds of undiagnosed cases in the state that's also home to the nation’s first confirmed infection and now the first death, researchers said Sunday after analyzing genetic samples of the pathogens.
snippet: The coronavirus may have been circulating for weeks undetected in Washington state, a preliminary finding that could mean hundreds of undiagnosed cases in the state that's also home to the nation’s first confirmed infection and now the first death...
lead_paragraph: PORTLAND, Ore. — The coronavirus may have been circulating for weeks undetected in Washington state, a preliminary finding that could mean hundreds of undiagnosed cases in the state that's also home to the nation’s first confirmed infection and now the first death, researchers said Sunday after analyzing genetic samples of the pathogens.
headline_main: Officials Seek to Calm Public as New US Virus Cases Reported
headline_print_headline: Officials Seek to Calm Public as New US Virus Cases Reported

abstract: The owners of a Mexican restaurant in the Tucson area are fending off social media attacks after appearing in the VIP area at President Donald Trump's Phoenix campaign rally last week.
snippet: The owners of a Mexican restaurant in the Tucson area are fending off social media attacks after appearing in the VIP area at President Donald Trump's Phoenix campaign rally last week.
lead_paragraph: TUCSON, Ariz. — The owners of a Mexican restaurant in the Tucson area are fending off social media attacks after appearing in the VIP area at President Donald Trump's Phoenix campaign rally last week.
headline_main: Arizona Restaurateurs Get Backlash Over Support of Trump
headline_print_headline: Arizona Restaurateurs Get Backlash Over Support of Trump

abstract: Any reservations Afghanistan has with Islamabad should be resolved bilaterally rather than involving the United States, Pakistan’s foreign minister said on Sunday, in reference to part of a joint U.S.-Afghan declaration on peace efforts.
snippet: Any reservations Afghanistan has with Islamabad should be resolved bilaterally rather than involving the United States, Pakistan’s foreign minister said on Sunday, in reference to part of a joint U.S.-Afghan declaration on peace efforts.
lead_paragraph: ISLAMABAD — Any reservations Afghanistan has with Islamabad should be resolved bilaterally rather than involving the United States, Pakistan’s foreign minister said on Sunday, in reference to part of a joint U.S.-Afghan declaration on peace efforts.
headline_main: No Need to Involve U.S. to Resolve Bilateral Issues, Pakistan Tells Afghanistan
headline_print_headline: No Need to Involve U.S. to Resolve Bilateral Issues, Pakistan Tells Afghanistan
